

Turnstyle v0.4

Promotional Campaign Builder & Compliance Automation Platform

⸻

1. System Overview

Turnstyle is a modular promotional campaign automation platform built to:
	•	Capture structured campaign configuration data
	•	Dynamically generate pricing and compliance outputs
	•	Produce abbreviated and full terms & conditions
	•	Manage internal approvals
	•	Generate QR and public-facing outputs
	•	Maintain structured campaign records

The system is currently built on:
	•	WordPress (CPT architecture)
	•	Elementor (UI layer)
	•	Custom Turnstyle plugins (business logic layer)
	•	REST endpoints for ingestion and storage

⸻

2. Authentication & Entry Layer

Login / Access

User enters via:
	•	Root 5-character campaign routing
	•	Admin login
	•	Builder access page

The system resolves:
	•	ts_code
	•	ts_post_id
	•	User role / session state

Validation ensures:
	•	Valid campaign ID
	•	Authorized access
	•	Required fields present before progression

⸻

3. Campaign Build Form (Campaign Configuration Engine)

Function:

Collect structured campaign parameters.

Captured Data Model:
	•	Campaign name
	•	Promoter entity
	•	Promotion dates
	•	Mechanic type
	•	Entry mechanic
	•	Regions / states
	•	Prize tiers
	•	Prize values
	•	Draw frequency
	•	Contact details

Output:

Creates or updates a Campaign CPT record.

Stored as:
	•	Post meta
	•	Structured JSON payload
	•	Version controlled

Validation:
	•	Required field enforcement
	•	Date logic validation
	•	Conditional visibility rules
	•	Prize value calculation cross-check

⸻

4. Command Centre (Campaign Control Panel)

Function:

Central operational dashboard for a campaign.

Displays:
	•	Campaign metadata
	•	Quote status
	•	Terms status
	•	Approval state
	•	Generated assets
	•	QR code
	•	Version history

Acts as orchestration layer between:
	•	Summary Editor
	•	Quote Engine
	•	Terms Engine
	•	Approval Panel

⸻

5. Quote Builder (Commercial Engine)

Function:

Calculate campaign cost dynamically.

Components:
	•	Terms drafting fee
	•	Management fee
	•	Permit fee logic (state-based threshold logic)
	•	Draw management
	•	Prize tiers complexity

Logic:
	•	Rule-based pricing engine
	•	Conditional pricing adjustments
	•	GST handling

Output:
	•	Structured quote object
	•	HTML export
	•	Email trigger
	•	Status: Draft → Approved

Stored in:
	•	Post meta
	•	JSON object
	•	Snapshot at approval

⸻

6. Summary Editor (Structured Campaign Narrative Engine)

Function:

Editable structured narrative derived from campaign data.

Two-way relationship:

When Build Form Updates:
	•	Summary auto-populates structured content

When Summary Editor Changes:
	•	Summary changes update stored meta
	•	Command Centre reflects changes
	•	Quote recalculates if dependent fields altered
	•	Abbreviated Terms regenerate

This creates a reactive data chain.

⸻

7. Quote Approval Panel

Function:

Formal commercial authorization gate.

On Approval:
	•	Stores:
	•	Approved by
	•	Timestamp
	•	Total ex GST
	•	Locks commercial snapshot
	•	Enables:
	•	Abbreviated Terms
	•	Full Terms Wizard
	•	Final outputs

Acts as system unlock trigger.

⸻

8. Abbreviated Terms Engine

Function:

Generate compliant short-form promotional terms.

Logic:
	•	Pulls structured campaign data
	•	Injects into templated legal clauses
	•	State permit references
	•	Draw details
	•	Prize descriptions

Output:
	•	HTML export
	•	PDF-ready
	•	Versioned

Templates stored as:
	•	Structured clause libraries
	•	Token-based merge variables
	•	CPT or database stored legal blocks

⸻

9. QR Code Generator

Function:

Generate public entry QR linked to:
	•	Campaign URL
	•	Landing page
	•	Entry endpoint

Uses:
	•	Campaign ID routing
	•	Root-based short routing
	•	Dynamic generation via library

Stored as:
	•	Image asset
	•	Embedded display in Command Centre

⸻

10. Full Terms Wizard (Post-Approval Legal Builder)

Triggered only after:
	•	Quote status = Approved

Function:

Step-by-step structured full legal document generator.

Flow:
	1.	Campaign core data locked
	2.	Wizard collects advanced legal nuance
	3.	Conditional clauses injected
	4.	State-specific compliance logic applied
	5.	Prize structure clauses expanded
	6.	Draw procedure detail inserted
	7.	Dispute & liability clauses appended

Templates:
	•	Modular clause storage
	•	Jurisdiction-based variants
	•	Permit-threshold logic blocks

Output:
	•	Full T&Cs HTML
	•	PDF export
	•	Versioned record
	•	Approval timestamp

⸻

11. Data Flow Architecture (Current WordPress Model)